        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.10"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Laird Memorial Hospital
                        <lb/>
                    Montgomery,West Virginia
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 6, 1948</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You have been continually in mind. Doctor Vining is at the hospital very frequently, and far oftener than you think you are the subject of our conversation.</p>
                
                <p>For many outstanding kindnesses I am indebted to our mutual friend, Doctor House. At the head of the long list is the introduction to your work.</p> 
                
                <p>When that was followed by the introduction to you in person, my cup was full to overflowing.</p>
                
                <p>Your presence at our home is one of my most gracious memories. It was a dream come true.</p>
                
                <p>And your brief sojourn at the hospital was a benediction to more people than you can imagine.</p>
                
                <p>Doctor Vining as usual is living most usefully. At long last I believe perhaps he is getting convinced of his usefulness. Perhaps he is getting a bit of happiness out of it.</p>
                
                <p>Mrs. Laird joins me in affectionate greetings. Please include Mrs. Neihardt in our salutations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Faithfully yours,</salute>
                    <signed>William R. Laird</signed>
                    <signed>William R. Laird.</signed>
                
                    <note>WRL/rma</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipeint">ansd</note>
                
            </div1>
